{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"alias":"upperclass-allied-walleye","description":"## Why\n\nADR 0017 and `.rebar/criteria_routing.json` advertise one project-criteria extension surface across\nplan review and code review, but the current code-review runtime only executes the static workflow\nlist and consults packaged decision/eval lookups. A project can therefore configure a net-new\nLLM-backed code-review criterion that merges successfully yet never runs end to end.\n\n## What\n\nComplete the generic, project-id-agnostic code-review runtime seam. The child bug\n`8a4b-e8b6-1bf9-48d8` owns the reproduced defect and implementation details. This story owns the\ndelivered capability and compatibility contract: activated project criteria run exactly once,\ntheir repository prompt and eval assets resolve, and deterministic Pass 3 uses repository-effective\nrouting.\n\n## Scope\n\n- Reuse plan review's runner-side dynamic fan-in pattern without adding a workflow DSL field or a\n  hard-coded project criterion id.\n- Resolve project prompt/eval assets from the reviewed repository snapshot and report located\n  configuration errors for activated missing or malformed assets.\n- Preserve the existing behavior and result shape for repositories without a code-review project\n  overlay.\n- Update `docs/llm-framework.md` to describe code-review project-criterion runtime resolution,\n  configuration failures, and the eval entry point, completing rather than replacing ADR 0017.\n\nOut of scope: authoring `project.review-phase-boundaries`, changing four-pass decision math,\nmodifying packaged built-in criteria, or deploying a Gerrit criterion.\n\n## Sequencing and Rollback\n\nThe child bug is implemented and closed before this story closes. Downstream criterion authoring\ndepends on this story. Revert the fan-in, routing lookup, eval resolution, tests, and documentation\ntogether if overlay-absent compatibility regresses; the additive seam has no data migration.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Child bug `8a4b-e8b6-1bf9-48d8` is closed and its change is landed on `main`; verify with\n  `.venv/bin/rebar show 8a4b-e8b6-1bf9-48d8` and\n  `git log origin/main --oneline --grep='rebar-ticket: 8a4b-e8b6-1bf9-48d8'`.\n- [ ] A synthetic activated code-review `project.*` criterion runs exactly once in Pass 1, retains\n  its logical criterion id, and resolves its repository prompt/eval assets; verify with\n  `.venv/bin/pytest -q tests/unit/test_code_review_project_criteria.py -k 'fan_in or eval'`.\n- [ ] Pass 3 applies repository-effective threshold, blocking posture, and nit-suppression routing\n  for the synthetic id without invoking an LLM; verify with\n  `.venv/bin/pytest -q tests/unit/test_code_review_project_criteria.py -k routing`.\n- [ ] Activated missing/malformed project assets produce located configuration errors and an\n  overlay-absent repository retains its pre-change result; verify with\n  `.venv/bin/pytest -q tests/unit/test_code_review_project_criteria.py -k 'missing or parity'`.\n- [ ] `docs/llm-framework.md` documents the completed code-review project-criterion runtime and the\n  focused regression suites pass; verify with\n  `.venv/bin/pytest -q tests/unit/test_unified_criteria.py tests/unit/test_code_review_evals.py\n  tests/unit/workflow/test_code_review_workflow.py && make lint`.","id":"2c14-fa5f-1228-4e02","parent_id":"jira-reb-1001","priority":1,"tags":["review-architecture","project-criteria","integration"],"ticket_type":"story","title":"Complete the generic code-review project-criterion runtime seam"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1784317556157853001,"uuid":"58403b9d-63aa-41fe-a3c5-2d7b67e898c4"}